# Testing Guidelines

## Test Organization

- **Unit Tests**: Written in the same file as the code being tested
- **Integration Tests**: Located in [tests/](mdc:tests/) directory
- **Test Categories**:
  - [tests/basic_commands/](mdc:tests/basic_commands/) - Basic CLI functionality
  - [tests/c_compilation/](mdc:tests/c_compilation/) - C code compilation tests
  - [tests/common/](mdc:tests/common/) - Shared test utilities

## Test Execution

Use the [Makefile](mdc:Makefile) for running tests:

- `make test-all` - Run all tests in Docker
- `make test-unit` - Run unit tests only
- `make test-integration` - Run integration tests
- `make test-verbose` - Run tests with verbose output
- `make test-crate CRATE=name` - Test specific crate

## Test Environment

- Tests run in isolated Docker containers via [docker/docker-compose.test.yml](mdc:docker/docker-compose.test.yml)
- Uses separate test Dockerfile for consistent environment
- Tests have access to all necessary system tools and dependencies

## Writing Tests

- Use `#[cfg(test)]` for test-only code
- Use `#[tokio::test]` for async tests
- Use `tracing` for test logging
- Test both success and failure cases
- Test edge cases and error conditions
- Use descriptive test names

## Test Dependencies

From workspace [Cargo.toml](mdc:Cargo.toml):

- `tokio` with `test-util` feature for async testing
- `tower` for HTTP testing utilities
- `tempfile` for temporary file operations

## Security Testing

- Test sandbox isolation
- Test input validation
- Test resource limits
- Test privilege escalation prevention
- Test system call filtering
